<paragraph blockId="2.[166,794,1033,1908]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[166,323,1033,1057]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Type material</emphasis>
. I made the following notes on type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel, Bronte" authorityYear="1914" box="[196,313,1062,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Microepicausta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[196,313,1062,1086]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">M. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in MNM, Budapest, in 
<date box="[570,690,1062,1086]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" value="1973-04">April 1973</date>
: 
<typeStatus box="[702,794,1062,1086]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[166,186,1088,1115]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, i.e. specimen of which both head and wing were figured [
<bibRefCitation author="Hendel, F." box="[172,329,1121,1145]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" refId="ref4315" refString="Hendel, F. 1914 a. Diptera, Fam. Muscaridae, Subfam. Platystominae. Genera Insectorum 157: 179 pp., 15 pls." type="book" year="1914">Hendel, 1914a</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 5, figs 101, 102], 
<collectingCountry box="[547,645,1121,1145]" name="Australia" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Australia</collectingCountry>
, L. Biró 1900, Sydney Botany B. Second specimen 
<specimenCount box="[561,581,1151,1174]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, same data, is not a type, though labelled as such. Third specimen of series, also labelled “type” is a small 
<specimenCount box="[429,449,1209,1232]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[480,718,1209,1233]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Rhytidortalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugifrons">
<emphasis box="[480,718,1209,1233]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Rhytidortalis rugifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I have labelled it so, but the species is now provisionally given as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomson)" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" box="[166,477,1267,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Duomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugifrons">
<emphasis box="[166,359,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Duomyia rugifrons</emphasis>
(Thomson)
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="McAlpine, D. K." box="[610,790,1267,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" pagination="147 - 174" refId="ref4503" refString="McAlpine, D. K. 2000. Australian signal flies of the genus Rhytidortalis (Diptera: Platystomatidae). Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales 121: 147 - 174 [Dated 1999, published 22 February 2000]." type="journal article" year="2000">McAlpine (2000)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
